            "question": {
              "en": {
                "comprehension": null,
                "direction": null,
                "content": "<p>In a photoelectric effect setup, silver metal emits photoelectrons when light of wavelength 256.7 nm falls on it. It is found that applying a stopping potential of 0.35 V just prevents the photoelectrons from reaching the collector. Determine the work function of silver.</p>",
                "options": [
