              "en": {
                "comprehension": null,
                "direction": null,
                "content": "<p>The radius of a hydrogen atom is approximately 0.05 nm, while the radius of its proton (nucleus) is $1.5 \\times 10^{-15}$ m. Treating both the hydrogen atom and the proton as spheres, find the fraction of the total volume of a hydrogen atom that is occupied by its nucleus.</p>",
